# Shamiso Design and Color Continuity

Apply these rules whenever creating or updating UI so new pages match existing Shamiso patterns.

- Keep the dark-first visual system: black or near-black backgrounds, white or neutral foreground text, and subtle glow or gradient accents.
- Reuse the established accent language (primarily sky/blue accents and neutral grayscale hierarchy); avoid introducing new dominant brand colors.
- Preserve existing spacing rhythm and typography scale used across marketing, dashboard, and service pages.
- Use existing UI primitives from `src/components/ui/*` (`Card`, `Button`, `Badge`, etc.) before creating custom visual patterns.
- Keep page composition consistent: clear hero or intro block, supporting sections, and strong CTA placement near key decision points.
- Match current border radius, shadow, and contrast patterns; favor subtle depth over heavy visual effects.
- Keep iconography consistent with current Lucide usage and existing component style.
- Prefer updating `PARTNER_LINKS` and shared components instead of hardcoding one-off styles or URLs in pages.
- Maintain responsive behavior using the same Tailwind breakpoint conventions already used in the app (`sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`).

## Do Not

- Do not introduce a new color system for individual pages.
- Do not create isolated page-specific style conventions that diverge from existing patterns.
- Do not bypass shared layout and chrome patterns when a reusable project pattern already exists.
